metadata.name: Sleepless in Los Angeles
metadata.description:
As I lay by the pool, the water's gentle ripples lulling me into a sense of calm, I felt a freedom that had long eluded me. Insomnia had been my constant companion for years, but at that moment, as I let the pool's waters soothe me, I was finally able to escape its grasp.

More details about this piece can be found in discord: discord.gg/FMFaRreAtV

For the limited edition, signed prints of other photographs, visit www.waytoomad.com.
